<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-60-0233 </DOCNO><TEXT>Limited recourse project financing in which project risks are shared bysponsors, international commercial banks and others has emerged as animportant financing method for resource projects, including coal projects.This type of finance can offer a number of advantages to coal mine developers,including: larger amounts of project debt may be raised against the reserves,projected cash flows and sales contracts than might otherwise be raisedthrough more traditional corporate finance; project finance is often'off balance sheet' debt in the books of the project developers; thewide range of risks involved in major coal projects can be spread amongsta number of parties; and project finance may also offer the advantageof tying in the valuable support of third parties which can benefit theproject sponsors over a long term. 3 figs.</TEXT></DOC>